  <amendments/>
  <summary>9/23/1997--Introduced.
Amends the Internal Revenue Code to revise the aggregate amount of credits allowed so that such amount shall not exceed the sum of: (1) the taxpayer's regular tax liability; plus (2) the alternative minimum tax amount. Permits the standard deduction and the deduction for personal exemptions to be used in calculating alternative minimum taxable income.</summary>
